1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,723
Now turn the method into one AI Agent Acceptance Sheet.

2
00:00:03,673 --> 00:00:10,894
Use it for a single high-value task before a release, for a repeated workflow, or as the seed of a larger evaluation suite.

3
00:00:10,894 --> 00:00:12,740
Block one is Outcome.

4
00:00:12,740 --> 00:00:19,759
Name the user-visible result, the final state that proves it exists, the acceptance threshold, and the evidence location.

5
00:00:19,759 --> 00:00:22,846
Do not use “Agent said done” as evidence.

6
00:00:22,846 --> 00:00:25,000
Block two is Task Setup.

7
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:31,634
Record the input, tools, permissions, starting state, important constraints, and a reference solution.

8
00:00:31,634 --> 00:00:36,836
This makes the task reproducible and exposes whether the environment itself creates noise.

9
00:00:36,836 --> 00:00:39,067
Block three is Grader Mix.

10
00:00:39,067 --> 00:00:47,221
Choose deterministic checks for objective state, model rubrics for open-ended quality, and human review for calibration or expert judgment.

11
00:00:47,221 --> 00:00:51,923
Give each grader one clear dimension instead of one grader an undefined job.

12
00:00:51,923 --> 00:00:54,086
Block four is Reliability.

13
00:00:54,086 --> 00:00:59,894
Set the number of trials, the metric that matches the product need, and the minimum acceptable result.

14
00:00:59,894 --> 00:01:05,586
One success may be enough for exploration, but repeated customer actions need a consistency bar.

15
00:01:05,586 --> 00:01:08,375
Block five is Eval Health and Decision.

16
00:01:08,375 --> 00:01:17,692
Record transcript spot checks, known grader gaps, environment failures, exceptions, the release decision, and the next failure that should become a new task.

17
00:01:17,692 --> 00:01:21,528
The sheet evaluates both the Agent and your confidence in the test.

18
00:01:21,528 --> 00:01:25,548
First, write the outcome and task setup before choosing a grader.

19
00:01:25,548 --> 00:01:30,951
Second, collect final-state evidence, behavior evidence, and repeated trials.

20
00:01:30,951 --> 00:01:35,682
Third, record the release decision, exceptions, and next test to add.
